Mobile App Automation with Appium and Java 

Introduction to Mobile App Automation and Appium 

Understand the importance and benefits of mobile app automation and the role of Appium. (1 hour) 

Study resources: 

Introduction to Mobile App Automation (https://www.softwaretestinghelp.com/mobile-automation-testing-tutorial-1/) 

Appium official website (http://appium.io/) 

Java Basics 

Familiarize yourself with the fundamentals of the Java programming language. (15 hours) 

Study resources: 

Java tutorials and documentation (https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/) 

(https://www.w3schools.com/java/java_intro.asp) 

"Java: A Beginner's Guide" by Herbert Schildt 

Codecademy's Java course (https://www.codecademy.com/learn/learn-java) 

Setting up the Development Environment 

Install the Java Development Kit (JDK) and set up environment variables. (2 hours) 

Choose an Integrated Development Environment (IDE) and configure it for Java development. (2 hours) 

Understanding Mobile App Automation Concepts 

Learn about mobile app automation concepts, including UI elements, gestures, and mobile platforms. (4 hours) 

Study resources: 

Mobile App Automation Concepts (https://www.softwaretestinghelp.com/mobile-automation-testing-tutorial-2/) 

Introduction to Appium 

Understand the features and capabilities of Appium for mobile app automation. (2 hours) 

Study resources: 

Appium documentation (http://appium.io/docs/en/about-appium/intro/) 

Setting up Appium and Device Configuration 

Install and configure Appium server and set up device emulators or physical devices. (3 hours) 

Study resources: 

Appium documentation: Getting Started (http://appium.io/docs/en/about-appium/getting-started/) 

Desired Capabilities and App Installation 

Learn how to define desired capabilities and install mobile apps for automation. (4 hours) 

Study resources: 

Appium documentation: Desired Capabilities (http://appium.io/docs/en/writing-running-appium/caps/) 

Locating Elements and Interacting with Mobile Apps 

Explore various methods to locate elements in mobile apps and perform interactions. (6 hours) 

Study resources: 

Appium documentation: Finding Elements (http://appium.io/docs/en/commands/element/find-elements/) 

Appium documentation: Touch Actions (http://appium.io/docs/en/commands/interactions/touch-actions/) 

Handling Mobile App Contexts 

Understand how to switch between native and web contexts in mobile apps. (4 hours) 

Study resources: 

Appium documentation: Contexts (http://appium.io/docs/en/commands/context/) 

Mobile App Testing Techniques 

Learn about mobile app testing techniques, including functional testing, performance testing, and compatibility testing. (3 hours) 

Study resources: 

Mobile App Testing Techniques (https://www.softwaretestinghelp.com/mobile-app-testing-techniques/) 

Test Frameworks and Integration  

Explore popular Java test frameworks with TestNG and integrate Appium with them. (6 hours) 

Study resources: 

TestNG documentation (https://testng.org/doc/documentation-main.html) 

